# {{ hostname }} Static Site + API

This scaffold combines a static nginx site with a small Python API behind the same hostname.

## Files

- `docker-compose.yml`: two services behind Traefik
- `.dockerignore`: keeps local cache, env, and Python bytecode noise out of the image build context
- `html/index.html`: starter static page
- `html/favicon.svg`: starter favicon
- `html/assets/css/main.css`: starter stylesheet
- `html/assets/js/main.js`: starter frontend script that calls the API
- `html/assets/images/.gitkeep`: placeholder so the images directory is tracked
- `api/Dockerfile`: container build for the API service
- `api/requirements.txt`: starter dependency file
- `api/app/main.py`: simple JSON API
- `README.md`: quick notes for the scaffold

## First run

1. Edit `html/index.html` with your real page content.
2. Replace `html/favicon.svg` when you are ready.
3. Update `api/app/main.py` with your real API behavior.
4. Start the stack with `docker compose up --build`.
5. Verify the containers become healthy.
6. Confirm `https://{{ hostname }}/` serves the frontend and `https://{{ hostname }}/api/status` returns JSON.

## Runtime behavior

- `site` serves files directly from `./html`
- `api` serves JSON from `./api`
- `GET /` serves the static page
- `GET /api/status` returns scaffold API JSON
- `GET /healthz` is used internally by the API healthcheck
